en.title: FE at Channel 7 Lifestyle Expo & Ironman Event Noosa, Australia 31st October 2008
en.content:
REPORT FROM AUSTRALIAN COUNTRY LICENSEE, MR. VASU THANDARAYAN:

FE Australia participates at Channel 7 LifeStyle EXPO and Ironman Event – NOOSA Queensland.

FE Australia continued its soft launch into Australia with its participation at the annual at Channel 7 LifeStyle EXPO and Ironman event – at the famous seaside holiday destination of NOOSA, Queensland. Some 7500 participants and over 20,000 spectators were in Noosa from all over the world. Many of the participants were amazed by the benefits of the Quantum Products and their unique properties.

Many of the participants who used the Quantum Products reported their best ever personal best performance. Lisa Licaari, an Olympic distance swimmer who a vertigo attack just a day before the event had had her best ever performance and improved her time by 12 minutes at the Noosa Ironman event.

FE members who took part were new members Slavko Jovicic, Christina Zhao, Lily Soo, Rebecca Jacob and Pamela Howlett with 2 Presidential Directors from KL - Rachel Thomas and Patricia Thava strongly supported the Australian FE team. FE Australia participation at the event was organised by Australian Country Licensee, Vasu and made possible with the strong support from FE Kuala Lumpur.
